<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 01 at 7:02PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...A BAND OF INTENSE SNOW SHOWERS...
At 658 PM MDT, a band of rain and snow showers was located along a
line extending from 12 miles south of Grass Range to 13 miles
northwest of Columbus. Movement was east at 40 mph.
Locations impacted include...
Columbus, Big Timber, Harlowton, Ryegate, Reed Point, Shawmut,
Greycliff and Rapelje.
This band may produce brief intense snow showers along with wind
gusts up to 50 mph. Roads may quickly become slushy and slick. Be
prepared for hazardous driving conditions as this band of snow
showers moves through.</description>
